news.title: Private equity inflow in real estate declines 44% to USD 3 billion so far this year: Knight Frank
news.para: Knight Frank India released its data showing that the Indian real estate market received USD 3,024 million in PE investments from 23 deals between January 1 and December 12 this year, as against USD 5,357 million recorded in 2022.

news.title: Violations many, flat extensions cut to 0.75m in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: The limit, which has been ambiguous till now, allowed people to build ramps that encroach upon roads. The slope gradient of the ramp should be in the 1:8 ratio.

news.title: MCD serves eviction notices to flat owners in all towers of Signature View Apartments
news.para: RWA secretary of Signature View Apartments, Gaurav Pandey, said that the notices were placed in four blocks by the MCD staff and it applied to all the apartments in 12 towers.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency plea against Ansal Properties' promoter
news.para: NCLT's has directed the appointment of Roshan Lal Jain as the resolution professional to verify the claims made by Indian Bank against Ansal. Indian Bank has claimed that Ansal has defaulted on dues of ₹76 crore for which payment was personally guaranteed by him.

news.title: Brigade Group lease out 54,000 sq ft office space to Sidvin Core-Tech India
news.para: Brigade Deccan Heights spans 2.2 acres with a 4.3 lakh sq ft development area.

news.title: MakeMyTrip's CEO, Genpact's CHRO buys apartment in Gurugram for around Rs 33 crore each
news.para: All three Golf Links projects — the Aralias, the Magnolias, and the Camellias — have witnessed significant price increases since last year as same sized apartment was sold at Rs 19 crore in October 2022.

news.title: Sahithi Infra land scam: ED attaches Rs 161 crore properties of accused
news.para: ED initiated attachment proceedings under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act based on the cheating cases registered by the Telangana police against the Sahithi Infratech and its promoters.

news.title: Bombay HC refuses to condone delay by Radius Group's MD in filing revision plea
news.para: ​​The Central Bureau of Investigation in April last year arrested Chhabria in a case of alleged corruption against Yes Bank founder Rana Kapoor and Dewan Housing Finance Corporation Ltd (DHFL).

news.title: Spain's Santander to buy stake in US real estate portfolio for $1.1 billion
news.para: The $9 billion portfolio of New York based multifamily real estate assets was in the hands of the FDIC following the failure of Signature Bank in the United States earlier this year.

news.title: Signa dissolves two top oversight bodies
news.para: The other dissolved body is an advisory board that included Signa founder Rene Benko, a former Austrian chancellor, and prominent figures in German and Swiss business.

news.title: SRA issues order to stop all projects activities in Mumbai's koliwadas
news.para: The SRA officials said that no SRA project will be considered in koliwadas and gaothans till either the urban development department comes up with special development rules for koliwadas and gaothans or till the state revenue department demarcates the boundaries of koliwada and gaothans across the city.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of five companies on January 22
news.para: ​The other firms whose properties will be auctioned are Just-Reliable Projects India Ltd, Orion Industries, and Rakhal Bharoti group of companies.

news.title: Ensure companies run own offices on allotted plots & not rent them: Uttar Pradesh govt
news.para: On Tuesday, Manoj Kumar Singh, the UP infrastructure and industrial development commissioner, issued a directive to all six industrial development authorities in the state including Noida and Greater Noida.

news.title: CAG questions allotment of 178 industrial plots in Maharashtra
news.para: MIDC defended its decisions, stating that they were made on merit and to meet specific demands. The CAG report recommended strict implementation of regulations and policies in land allotment and recovery of charges.

news.title: Bandhan Bank to transfer housing finance NPAs to asset reconstruction company
news.para: The outstanding amount that will be transferred to the company is Rs 775.62 crore as on September 30, 2023. The lender had received a binding bid of Rs 280.39 crore for the NPA portfolio on outright cash consideration basis, it said.

news.title: CMDA bats for holistic growth in Chennai's five-fold expansion
news.para: CMDA floated tenders last week to appoint a consultant to carry out a study titled ‘Sustainable Economic Growth Strategic Plan in Chennai Metropolitan Area’.

news.title: Delhi HC asks Centre to consider representation for linking property with Aadhaar
news.para: The court was hearing a petition by lawyer Ashwini Kumar Upadhyay, who said it is the duty of the state to take appropriate steps to curb corruption and seize 'benami' properties amassed by illegal means to give a strong message that the government is determined to fight corruption and black money generation.

news.title: Sachin Tendulkar's company leases two apartments in Mumbai's Bandra
news.para: Both the apartments leased by the company are spread over 3,358 sq ft on the fifth floor of project Raheja Bay and the company has leased them directly from the developer Ferani Developers.

news.title: NCLT approves Rs 595 crore settlement offer for Hotel Le Royal Meridien in Chennai & Coimbatore
news.para: This is a rare instance wherein lenders will recover their entire dues. In most resolutions under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC), lenders have recovered less than 30% of dues on average.

news.title: Commercially used residential places under Nashik civic body's radar
news.para: An NMC official, while talking to TOI, said it is mandatory for the property owners to take permission if they are carrying out commercial activities in residential units and must pay the property tax as per the commercial rates.
